    "/home/michael/prj/nu-agent/README.md",
    "ddb81ff5a38f47ee13d4d9a010ee2d30744a848d5c93f1d7a755751c73e59690",
    nu-agent,
    [
      Usage
    ],
    "Example with Nushell:
```nu
use ./mod.nu *
airun --task \"refactor\"

```
Single-item enrichment example:
```nu
use ./mod.nu *
enrich --task \"annotate workout\" --record '{\"exercise\":\"squat\",\"reps\":5}' --schema '{\"allowed\":[\"label\",\"notes\"],\"required\":[\"label\"],\"non_null\":[\"label\"]}'

```
Repo-local CLI wrapper for enrichment:
```bash
NU_AGENT_CHAT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1/chat/completions ./nu-agent --task \"annotate workout\" --record '{\"exercise\":\"squat\",\"reps\":5}' --schema '{\"allowed\":[\"label\"],\"required\":[\"label\"],\"non_null\":[\"label\"]}'

```
Deterministic local execution test (no LLM):
```nu
use ./mod.nu *
run-json --calls '[{\"name\":\"list-files\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\".\"}}]'

```
Build a minimal RAG bundle from Markdown:
```bash
nu scripts/prep-nu-rag.nu --input README.md --out-dir build/rag/demo

```
This wipes the prior 
``build/nu_ingest``
/
``data``
 directories (with 
``--force``
), runs the shredder over the input, materialises the command map and chunk stores, andŌĆöif the 
``embed_runner``
 binary is availableŌĆöwrites deterministic embeddings under 
``build/rag/demo/embeddings/``
.
The helper leaves human-readable and machine-friendly copies of every artefact:
``build/rag/demo/data/nu_docs_vectors.nuon``
 and 
``data/nu_docs.msgpack``
``build/rag/demo/embedding_input/``
 with NUON, MsgPack, and JSON views
``build/rag/demo/embeddings/corpus.embeddings.msgpack``
 (when embeddings are generated)
From there you can query the corpus using the existing tools:
```nu
use ./tools.nu *
resolve-command-doc --name \"open\"
search-nu-concepts --query \"list files\" --limit 3

```
Graph/database import tooling is intentionally external. If you need a graph store or LanceDB dataset, implement it in a separate adapter and point it at the artefacts produced by the pipeline above.
Repo-local CLI wrapper:
```bash
NU_AGENT_CHAT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1/chat/completions ./nu-agent --task \"refactor\"

```
The CLI requires 
``NU_AGENT_CHAT_URL``
 so it points at your local or test LLM endpoint.

It prints a short notice before calling the model, since some local models can take several minutes to respond.
",
