    [
      "Running the pipeline"
    ],
    "Build the Rust helpers once
```bash
cargo build --manifest-path crates/nu_plugin_rag/Cargo.toml

```
This produces 
``target/debug/embed_runner``
 and 
``target/debug/nu-search``
, which

the scripts rely on when generating embeddings and running smoke searches.
Ingest Markdown and generate embeddings
```bash
nu scripts/prep-nu-rag.nu --input https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io.git --out-dir build/rag/nu-docs

```
The wrapper clones the repository if needed, runs the shredder over every

Markdown file, builds the command map and chunk stores, and (when

``embed_runner``
 is available) writes deterministic embeddings to

``build/rag/nu-docs/embeddings/``
.
Optional manual control
If you prefer to run the steps individually, see

``docs/RAG_HAPPY_PATH.md``
 for the exact commands (
``nu-shredder``
,

``scripts/make-data-from-chunks.nu``
, and 
``embed_runner``
).
Querying the artefacts
```nu
use ./tools.nu *

resolve-command-doc --name \"open\"

search-nu-concepts --query \"pipeline\" --limit 3

```
You can also run 
``target/debug/nu-search``
 directly against the generated

embeddings for quick similarity checks.
",
